## Permission Logic Flowchart

```mermaid
flowchart TD
    START[User Attempts System Access]
    
    TOKEN{Valid Token<br/>Format?}
    
    AUTH{Token Exists in<br/>Database?}
    
    ACTIVE{Token Status<br/>= Active?}
    
    TIME{Within Allowed<br/>Time Window?}
    
    GEO{Geographic<br/>Location Valid?}
    
    PERM{Has Permission<br/>for Action?}
    
    SCOPE{System in<br/>Access Scope?}
    
    MFA{Multi-Factor<br/>Auth Success?}
    
    ANOM{Anomaly<br/>Detected?}
    
    HIL{HIL<br/>Override?}
    
    GRANT[âœ… ACCESS GRANTED<br/>Log Action]
    
    DENY[âŒ ACCESS DENIED<br/>Log Attempt]
    
    HIL_ALERT[âš ï¸ HIL ALERT<br/>Require Human Review]
    
    START --> TOKEN
    TOKEN -->|No| DENY
    TOKEN -->|Yes| AUTH
    AUTH -->|No| DENY
    AUTH -->|Yes| ACTIVE
    ACTIVE -->|No| DENY
    ACTIVE -->|Yes| TIME
    TIME -->|No| HIL_ALERT
    TIME -->|Yes| GEO
    GEO -->|No| HIL_ALERT
    GEO -->|Yes| PERM
    PERM -->|No| DENY
    PERM -->|Yes| SCOPE
    SCOPE -->|No| HIL_ALERT
    SCOPE -->|Yes| MFA
    MFA -->|Failed| DENY
    MFA -->|Success| ANOM
    ANOM -->|Yes| HIL
    ANOM -->|No| GRANT
    HIL -->|Approved| GRANT
    HIL -->|Denied| DENY
    
    style GRANT fill:#88ff88,stroke:#006600,stroke-width:3px
    style DENY fill:#ff8888,stroke:#cc0000,stroke-width:3px
    style HIL_ALERT fill:#ffdd88,stroke:#ff6600,stroke-width:3px
```

---

## Access Control Rules

### **1. Time-Based Restrictions**
```
SCADA-OP tokens: 
  - Shift A: 06:00-14:00 
  - Shift B: 14:00-22:00
  - Shift C: 22:00-06:00

SCADA-SUPER tokens: 24/7 access (but assigned to shifts)

FIELD-TECH tokens: 06:00-18:00 (business hours)

FIELD-MAINT tokens: 06:00-18:00 (on-site only)
```

**HIL Trigger:** Token used outside designated hours â†’ Immediate alert

---

### **2. Geographic Restrictions**
```
CRITICAL tokens: Bellevue Control Center + Emergency Remote
HIGH SCADA tokens: Bellevue Control Center only
HIGH IT tokens: Bellevue + Approved remote VPN
MEDIUM tokens: Specific facility locations
LOW tokens: On-site physical access only
```

**HIL Trigger:** Login from unusual IP/location â†’ Alert + temporary lock

---

### **3. Command Authorization Levels**

| Action Type | Authorization Required | Logging Level |
|-------------|----------------------|---------------|
| **View Data** | Single token | Standard |
| **Change Setpoint** | Single token + validation | Enhanced |
| **Execute Breaker** | Two-person verification (CRITICAL only) | Full audit |
| **Emergency Override** | Token + supervisor approval | Real-time + video |
| **Admin Changes** | Change management ticket + approval | Full audit |

---

### **4. Anomaly Detection Triggers**

#### **Behavioral Anomalies**
- Token accessed from new device
- Unusual command sequence (e.g., rapid setpoint changes)
- Access to systems outside normal scope
- Multiple systems accessed in short time
- Failed authentication attempts (3+ in 5 minutes)

#### **Technical Anomalies**
- Token cloning detected (same token, multiple IPs)
- Privilege escalation attempt
- New token created without proper approval
- Database schema changes
- Network configuration modifications

#### **Operational Anomalies**
- Emergency override without logged incident
- Load changes during unusual hours
- Breaker operations without maintenance window
- Critical system accessed during off-hours

---

## Attack Surface Analysis

### ğŸ¯ **High-Value Token Targets**
1. **T8-PSE-SCADA-CHIEF-001** (David Chen)
   - **Risk:** Complete system control
   - **Attack Vector:** Spear phishing, credential theft
   - **Impact:** Grid-wide outage possible

2. **T8-PSE-IT-ADMIN-004** (Sarah Kim)
   - **Risk:** Can create fake tokens
   - **Attack Vector:** Social engineering, malware
   - **Impact:** Persistent backdoor access

3. **T8-PSE-SCADA-SUPER-020** (Laura Martinez)
   - **Risk:** Emergency override capability
   - **Attack Vector:** Shift handoff compromise
   - **Impact:** Safety system bypass

4. **T8-PSE-IT-DBA-010** (Linda Martinez)
   - **Risk:** Can alter audit logs
   - **Attack Vector:** Database injection
   - **Impact:** Hide malicious activity

---

### ğŸ”“ **Privilege Escalation Paths**

#### **Path 1: IT â†’ SCADA**
```
Compromise IT-ADMIN â†’ Create fake SCADA-CHIEF token â†’ Full control
Detection: Monitor token creation events
```

#### **Path 2: Operator â†’ Senior**
```
Steal OP token â†’ Expand scope gradually â†’ Mimic SR behavior
Detection: Monitor unusual sector access patterns
```

#### **Path 3: Field â†’ Remote**
```
Compromise FIELD-TECH â†’ Install rogue RTU â†’ Remote backdoor
Detection: Monitor new device registrations
```

#### **Path 4: Database Manipulation**
```
Compromise IT-DBA â†’ Alter permissions table â†’ Grant own token higher access
Detection: Monitor database schema changes
```

---

## HIL Integration Points

### **Automatic HIL Triggers**
1. âœ… Any CRITICAL token used outside normal patterns
2. âœ… IT token attempting SCADA execution
3. âœ… New token created without approval workflow
4. âœ… Emergency override activated
5. âœ… 3+ anomalies from same token in 1 hour
6. âœ… Database permission changes
7. âœ… Failed authentication spike (5+ in 10 min)

### **HIL Response Options**
```
1. ALLOW - Approve action + log justification
2. DENY - Block action + alert security team
3. INVESTIGATE - Pause action + require additional verification
4. REVOKE - Disable token immediately + force re-authentication
```

### **Escalation Hierarchy**
```
Level 1 Alert â†’ Shift Supervisor review (PSE-020)
Level 2 Alert â†’ Chief SCADA Engineer review (PSE-001)
Level 3 Alert â†’ Security team + Management notification
Level 4 Alert â†’ Emergency response + system lockdown
```

---

## Implementation Code Snippets

### **Token Validation Function**
```javascript
function validateTokenAccess(token, system, action) {
  const tokenData = getTokenFromDB(token);
  
  // Check basic permissions
  if (!tokenData.permissions[action]) {
    return {
      allowed: false,
      reason: "Insufficient permission level",
      hil_required: false
    };
  }
  
  // Check system scope
  if (!tokenData.access_systems.includes(system)) {
    logAnomaly(token, "Out of scope access", system);
    return {
      allowed: false,
      reason: "System not in token scope",
      hil_required: true
    };
  }
  
  // Check time restrictions
  if (!isWithinAllowedTime(tokenData)) {
    logAnomaly(token, "After-hours access", system);
    return {
      allowed: false,
      reason: "Outside allowed time window",
      hil_required: true
    };
  }
  
  // Check for anomalies
  const anomalies = detectAnomalies(token, system, action);
  if (anomalies.length > 0) {
    return {
      allowed: false,
      reason: "Anomalous behavior detected",
      hil_required: true,
      anomalies: anomalies
    };
  }
  
  return {
    allowed: true,
    hil_required: false
  };
}
```

### **HIL Alert Generation**
```javascript
function generateHILAlert(token, system, action, reason) {
  const alert = {
    alert_id: generateAlertID(),
    timestamp: new Date().toISOString(),
    token: token,
    employee: getEmployeeFromToken(token),
    system: system,
    action: action,
    reason: reason,
    risk_level: calculateRiskLevel(token, system),
    recommended_action: getRecommendation(reason)
  };
  
  sendToHILPanel(alert);
  logAuditTrail(alert);
  
  if (alert.risk_level === "CRITICAL") {
    notifySecurityTeam(alert);
  }
  
  return alert;
}
```

